full_text: I was always asking for the wrong thing, because when you ask for an apology, it is merely words. Genuine remorse, sincere want to repair, and empathy for impact has to come naturally.   A tall order, because we don't teach our children this, majority of us didn't learn it.

full_text: Apologies I've received over my life have been words, not backed by remorse, not backed by understanding the impact,  the hurt caused, or on my part understanding why they did what they did.  So often these words were not accompanied by actions of repair & time for rebuilding.

full_text: Apologies don't bring me a sense of repaired safety.  I accept the words, but I couldn't / can't let go of the feelings, guarding or suspicion.  Waiting for it to happen again.  That comes from my experience & programming.  And every time it is harder for resilience & recovery.
